Unfortunately, the Firebase Realtime database does not support queries on multiple properties. It only supports queries on a single-child property. So there is no way you can get all trades where `offereeName` equals `Juan` and `offererName` equals `Pedro` in a single go.

To overcome this situation you&#39;ll have to create an extra field that should hold the value of both fields. So your node should look like this:

    db-root
     |
     --- Trade
          |
          --- -NH-Y...mH9e
                |
                --- offereeName: &quot;Juan&quot;
                |
                --- offererName: &quot;Pedro&quot;
                |
                --- offereeName_offererName: &quot;Juan_Pedro&quot;

As you can see, the `offereeName_offererName` filed combines the values that you want to filter on. So a query that looks like this:

    DatabaseReference db = FirebaseDatabase.getInstance().getReference();
	DatabaseReference tradeRef = db.child(&quot;Trade&quot;);
    Query query = tradeRef.orderByChild(&quot;offereeName_offererName&quot;).equalTo(&quot;Juan_Pedro&quot;);

